quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  10,34,"Say, \"Is there any of your associates who can originate a creation and then reproduce it?\" Say, \"Allah produces creation, then reproduces it. How then are you misled (deluded)"
  10,35,"Say, \"Is there any of your associates who guides unto the truth?\" Say, \"Allah guides unto the truth.\" Is then He who guides unto the truth more worthy to be followed, or he that guides not except he is himself guided? What ails you the"
  10,36,"But most of them follow naught but conjecture (suspicion, fancy, guesswork, speculation); verily, conjecture can by no means take the place of (or avail against) truth. Verily, Allah is Aware of what they do"
  10,37,"This Quran could not have been devised by any beside (or in opposition to) Allah; but it is a confirmation (or verification) of that which came before it, and a fuller explanation of the Book (Scriptures, or that which was decreed for mankind) - there is"
  10,38,"Do they say, \"He hath devised it\"? Say then, \"Bring a surah (chapter) like it, and call, if you can, on other than Allah, if you are truthful"
  10,39,"Yet they call that a lie the knowledge of which they cannot compass, even before its Taawil (interpretation, elucidation, explanation, fulfilment, effects) has reached them. Thus did those before them make charges of falsehood. But see what was the conseq"
  10,40,Of them are some who believe therein; and of them are some who do not believe therein; but your Lord is best aware of the corrupters
  10,41,"But if they deny you, say, \"I have my work, and you have your work; you are innocent of what I work, and I am innocent of what you work"
  10,42,"There are some of them who listen to you. But can you make the deaf to hear, when they have no understanding (or sense)"